In the MATTER OF JULIUS C. Administration for Children's Services, Respondent;
v.
Ebony W., Appellant; Julius C., et al., Nonparty-Respondents. 2017-1206 Court of Appeals of New York. February 13, 2018

(And Another Proceeding)

Motion for leave to appeal dismissed upon the ground that the order sought to be appealed from does not finally determine the proceeding within the meaning of the Constitution.

*1250**860Motion for poor person relief dismissed as academic.
